race.comment: TUNED (2) above average gelding with the early speed to get across from the wide gate. Clearly strengthened over the break and can go one better here over the 1300m. Gets weight relief with Nock's claim and sure to measure up. APPLAUD (13) appreciated the rain affected conditions first-up when a surprise winner from back in the field over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Best form is early in the prep and can go on with it today. BARTOLF (10) in career best form and returns from a let-up. Strong through the line when fourth to TUNED over 1200m here. Genuine top-three chance. SILVANITO (14) headed north to grab a last-start Doomben win and draws to be competitive.
